@spokehedz This is sort of correct. It does indeed break the sound barrier... I mean... after all... it is LIGHT, but yes it is caused by the heat. There is no sonic boom from light or lightning itself, but from the shockwaves coming rapid expansion of the gasses being heated up.

Light breaking the sound barrier does not cause sonic booms...
&quot;If this were true, then every time we turned on a light in the house we would hear a sonic boom!&quot;
